definition: old variant of 曆|历[li4]/old variant of 歷|历[li4]

sentences.english: The obvious place to start is Muscat.
sentences.chinese: 很显然，马斯喀特应该是游历阿曼开始的地方。

sentences.english: HereI will spread and share my traveling experiences one by one with you.
sentences.chinese: 这里且将我平生的游历逐一道来，与诸君共享。

sentences.english: He was China's most widely traveled senior diplomat.
sentences.chinese: 他是中国游历最广的一名高级外交官。

sentences.english: Among them, the second part is about the peregrination of Yang Shen in Yun nan.
sentences.chinese: 其中，第二部分专写杨慎的游历及交游情况。

sentences.english: After a week of traveling and seeing the amazing sights, I had aesthetic fatigue.
sentences.chinese: 经过一周的游历，我或多或少有些审美疲劳了。

sentences.english: Sync or Swim is a relaxing program that takes you on trips to the most extreme music and dance performance activities in the world.
sentences.chinese: 带你游历世界各地，欣赏各式各样的歌艺与舞蹈表演。

sentences.english: Baggins is the wandering Hobbit who found the Ring.
sentences.chinese: 巴金斯是常在外游历的霍比特人，正是他捡到了魔戒。

sentences.english: that I've been pulling across the states and Canada.
sentences.chinese: 我开着它游历了美国和加拿大各地。

sentences.english: He traveled to all the Free Cities, and Westeros as well.
sentences.chinese: 他游历过所有的自由城邦和维斯特洛伊大陆。

sentences.english: He experienced different cultures during his peregrination.
sentences.chinese: 在国外的游历使他体验到不同的文化。

sentences.english: She travels nationally and is regularly featured in yoga and health publications.
sentences.chinese: 她游历过许多国家，并能定期推荐瑜珈和健康出版物。

sentences.english: Han is well traveled, and claims to have been from one side of the galaxy to the other.
sentences.chinese: 汉游历甚广，并声称曾经横穿整个银河系。

sentences.english: By chance attendant who was to combat with wayfarer had only one eye.
sentences.chinese: 碰巧游历僧人的对手只有一只眼睛。

sentences.english: You said that you've travelled many different places in Europe. Which one is your favorite?
sentences.chinese: 你说你游历过欧洲许多地方。你最喜欢哪里？

sentences.english: Among the traveler's peregrinations , many can be named as adventures.
sentences.chinese: 在那位旅游者的游历中，有许多可以被称作冒险。

sentences.english: Seamen proudly sported earrings as a mark of their travels and voyages.
sentences.chinese: 水手们自豪地将耳环夸耀成他们游历和航海的标志。

definition: variant of 周遊|周游, to tour/to travel around
variant of 周遊|周游, to tour/to travel around
to wander (typically of an errant priest)
to study away from home or abroad (old)
to travel around many countries (idiom); peregrinations/refers to the travels of Confucius
to leave home to make one's way in the world/to leave the life one knows to seek success
to seek knowledge/to study/to attend college
to go on a scenic tour
to explore/to go on an expedition/adventure
